column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind Blowing Downstream
column14: Arc Lite ADCP measurement at gauge. Torrent board would likely be fine in this flow but wind is strong so glad to have Arc Lite. GPS Quakity 5. No moving bed, BT used. GPS quality improved to 4 during first transect. borted several transects with poor edges (ran aground on far bank, zero cells). GPS and BT nav tracks aligned well. Some variance between transects so completed 2 extra.De-selected the upper and lower extremes in QRev. One transect with >25% invalid eensembles but 52 samples collected. One or more transects have pitch exceeding calibration limits - suspect this was caused either by wind or when pushing boat away from edge.  @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Both sensors tracking well. ADCP by Moving Boat
HG: 1.603 HG2: 1.602 Surge: 0.025  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Found (FD)

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind Blowing Downstream
column14: GPS Quality 1. Unable to resolve. All lights are green, 10 sats in view, tried moving the base, no luck. GPS quality bumped up to 5 and then 4 during measurement. Disregard first transect - did not end starting edge. Moving bed found - used GGA. Disregarded two more transects after QRev review - one with zero discharge in an edge and a second with excessive boat movement. Remaining transects are reciprocal paris and have sufficient duration for measurement. @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Purged - HG RAW stable before and after so reset. Installed OTT PLS SN 463032 cable length. Need to trench line and tidy cabling in gauge next visit.Set HG2 to match HG at 14:21. ADCP by Moving Boat
HG: 1.643 Surge: 0.003  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Found (FD)
